---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import OvertimeCalculator from '../components/OvertimeCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Overtime Calculator — Calculate Overtime Pay | Clockr"
	description="Calculate overtime pay from your hourly rate, standard hours, and hours worked. Free overtime calculator with time-and-a-half and double-time multipliers."
	category="work"
>
	<div class="ot-page">
		<div class="ot-header">
			<div class="ot-eyebrow">
				<span class="ot-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				Work & Business
			</div>
			<h1 class="ot-title">
				<span class="ot-gradient">Overtime Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="ot-subtitle">Calculate your overtime pay quickly and accurately</p>
		</div>

		<OvertimeCalculator client:load />

		<section class="ot-how">
			<h2 class="ot-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="ot-how-card">
				<p>
					Overtime pay is compensation for hours worked beyond a standard workweek.
					Many employers pay extra for those hours using a multiplier on your
					regular hourly rate. The most common rates are time and a half (1.5× your
					base rate) and double time (2× your base rate), though the exact multiplier
					depends on your employer, role, and when the extra hours are worked.
				</p>
				<p>
					Overtime rules and entitlements vary significantly by country, industry,
					and individual employment contract. Some workers have a statutory right
					to enhanced pay above a weekly hour threshold; others rely entirely on
					what their contract states. This calculator is for general arithmetic
					only — it is not a substitute for checking your specific contractual or
					legal entitlements with your employer or a qualified adviser.
				</p>
				<p>
					Clockr splits your week into regular and overtime portions automatically.
					Regular hours are capped at your standard hours per week (default 40).
					Any hours above that threshold count as overtime and are multiplied by
					your chosen rate before being added to your regular pay for a weekly
					total.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="ot-faq">
			<h2 class="ot-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="ot-faq-list">
				<details class="ot-faq-item">
					<summary class="ot-faq-question">How is overtime pay calculated?</summary>
					<div class="ot-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Overtime pay is typically calculated by multiplying your regular
							hourly rate by an overtime multiplier (such as 1.5 or 2), then
							multiplying that enhanced rate by the number of overtime hours worked.
							Regular pay covers hours up to your standard week; overtime pay covers
							only the hours beyond that threshold. Total weekly pay is the sum of
							both amounts.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="ot-faq-item">
					<summary class="ot-faq-question">What is time and a half?</summary>
					<div class="ot-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Time and a half means your hourly rate multiplied by 1.5. If you earn
							£20 per hour, time and a half is £30 per hour for each qualifying
							overtime hour. It is one of the most widely used overtime multipliers,
							though not every employer or jurisdiction applies it in the same way.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="ot-faq-item">
					<summary class="ot-faq-question">What is double time?</summary>
					<div class="ot-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Double time means your hourly rate multiplied by 2. A £20 hourly rate
							becomes £40 per overtime hour at double time. Some employers offer
							double time for Sundays, public holidays, or hours beyond a second
							weekly threshold — but this varies widely and is often set out in
							employment contracts or collective agreements.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="ot-faq-item">
					<summary class="ot-faq-question">Is overtime pay required by law?</summary>
					<div class="ot-faq-answer">
						<p>
							It depends on where you work and your employment status. Some countries
							mandate overtime premiums for eligible employees above certain hour
							limits; others leave overtime pay to individual contracts. Exempt
							salaried roles, contractors, and part-time arrangements may be treated
							differently. Check your local employment rules and your contract for
							what applies to you.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="ot-faq-item">
					<summary class="ot-faq-question">How many hours is considered overtime?</summary>
					<div class="ot-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The overtime threshold is not universal. In the United States, 40 hours
							per workweek is a common federal benchmark for many non-exempt employees.
							In the UK and elsewhere, there is often no single statutory weekly
							limit — overtime may begin after your contracted hours, which could be
							35, 37.5, 40, or another figure. Set your standard hours in the
							calculator to match your own schedule.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="ot-faq-item">
					<summary class="ot-faq-question"
						>Does overtime pay vary by industry or country?</summary
					>
					<div class="ot-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes. Healthcare, hospitality, transport, and public-sector roles often
							have different overtime rules from office-based work. Countries differ
							in whether overtime is legally required, how the threshold is defined,
							and whether premiums apply on weekends or holidays. Union agreements
							and company policies can add further variation — always confirm the
							rate and rules that apply to your situation.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="ot-related">
			<h3 class="ot-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="ot-related-grid">
				<a href="/work-hours-calculator" class="ot-related-card"
					><span class="ot-related-name">Work Hours Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/business-days" class="ot-related-card"
					><span class="ot-related-name">Business Days Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/pomodoro-timer" class="ot-related-card"
					><span class="ot-related-name">Pomodoro Timer</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.ot-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.ot-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.ot-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.ot-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.ot-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.ot-gradient {
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.ot-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.ot-tool {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.ot-form-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 32px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.06);
	}

	.ot-inputs {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 24px;
		margin-bottom: 28px;
	}

	.ot-input-wrap {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 10px;
	}

	.ot-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		letter-spacing: 0.3px;
	}

	.ot-label--block {
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 12px;
	}

	.ot-rate-row {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.ot-currency {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 24px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}

	.ot-input {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		outline: none;
		width: 100%;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
		color-scheme: dark;
	}

	.ot-input--rate {
		font-size: 24px;
	}

	.ot-input--multiplier {
		max-width: 120px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.ot-input:focus {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
	}

	.ot-input::placeholder {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.ot-input-note {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.ot-multiplier-section {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.12);
		padding-top: 24px;
	}

	.ot-multiplier-btns {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 10px;
	}

	.ot-multiplier-btn {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 4px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 14px 10px;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease;
	}

	.ot-multiplier-btn:hover {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.6);
		background: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.08);
	}

	.ot-multiplier-btn--active {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-to-rgb), 0.7);
		background: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.12);
		box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.1);
	}

	.ot-multiplier-btn-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.ot-multiplier-btn-sub {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		text-align: center;
		line-height: 1.3;
	}

	.ot-custom-multiplier {
		margin-top: 16px;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 10px;
	}

	.ot-custom-row {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 12px;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.ot-custom-suffix {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
	}

	.ot-results {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 20px;
	}

	.ot-stats-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.ot-stat-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 20px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.ot-stat-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		margin-bottom: 8px;
		letter-spacing: 0.3px;
	}

	.ot-stat-num {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 28px;
		font-weight: 800;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
	}

	.ot-total-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.25);
		border-radius: 16px;
		padding: 28px;
		text-align: center;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.08);
	}

	.ot-total-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		margin-bottom: 12px;
		letter-spacing: 0.3px;
	}

	.ot-total-num {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 48px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -2px;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
	}

	.ot-table-wrap {
		overflow-x: auto;
	}

	.ot-table {
		width: 100%;
		border-collapse: collapse;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
	}

	.ot-table th,
	.ot-table td {
		padding: 14px 16px;
		text-align: left;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
	}

	.ot-table th {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
	}

	.ot-table td {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
	}

	.ot-table tfoot td {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		border-bottom: none;
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.2);
	}

	.ot-table tfoot td:last-child {
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		font-size: 16px;
	}

	.ot-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.ot-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.ot-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.ot-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.ot-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.ot-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.ot-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.ot-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.ot-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.ot-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.ot-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.ot-faq-item[open] .ot-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.ot-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.ot-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.ot-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.ot-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.ot-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.ot-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.ot-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.4);
	}

	.ot-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.ot-title {
			font-size: 48px;
		}

		.ot-multiplier-btns {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.ot-total-num {
			font-size: 36px;
		}

		.ot-stat-num {
			font-size: 22px;
		}
	}
</style>
